==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[despoliare]]''

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|despoil||}}

# {{transitive}} To [[strip]] of [[possession]]s; to [[divest]] or [[unclothe]]; to [[undress]].
# {{transitive}} To [[deprive]] for [[spoil]]; to take spoil from; to [[plunder]]; to [[rob]]; to [[pillage]].

